9. ExpressJS – Templating, Form Data, Cookies, Sessions 
a. Write a program using templating engine. 
A Templating Engine allows you to generate dynamic HTML pages by combining: 
 Static HTML 
 Dynamic data (variables, loops, conditions) 
Common templating engines used with Express: 
 EJS (Embedded JavaScript) 
 Pug 
 Handlebars 
Here we use EJS 
Why Templating Engine? 
 To pass data from server to HTML page 
 To display dynamic content 
 To reuse layouts 
const express = require('express'); 
const app = express(); 
app.set('view engine', 'ejs'); 
app.get('/', (req, res) => { 
res.render('index', {  
name: "Manikanta", 
course: "MERN Stack" 
}); 
}); 
app.listen(3000, () => { 
console.log("Server running on http://localhost:3000"); 
}); 
